This follows power outages in some parts of Johannesburg for over two days. JOHANNESBURG - City Power is expected to meet with contractors who are responsible for repairing damaged power cables. This follows power outages in some parts of Johannesburg over the last two days.City Power has blamed cable theft and recent cold weather for the power cuts.Spokesperson Virgil James says contractors need to repair the cables correctly. I can t name them, but they are causing damage. As much as they may be held liable, the immediate problem is felt by residents. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)